1:1 COMMENT "# generator_bidirectional.z -- generator that receives values back"
1:67 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# from the caller."
2:19 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "#"
3:2 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# Declaring `accepts: <U>` in the iterator return type lets each"
4:65 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# `.call value: <U>` deposit a value into the iterator before the"
5:66 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# state machine resumes. Inside the body, expression-form"
6:58 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# `name: yield v` binds `name` to that received value on the"
7:61 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# corresponding resumption. The first `.call` receives no value"
8:64 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# (the resume-input slot is undefined before any input arrives),"
9:65 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# so the first reachable yield must be statement form (rule 11)."
10:65 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "#"
11:2 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# The for-loop only drives `accepts: null` generators; a"
12:57 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# bidirectional generator is driven manually via `with`/`.call"
13:63 EOL "\n"
14:1 COMMENT "# value: ...`. See doc/spec.pdoc Generator functions."
14:54 EOL "\n"
15:1 COMMENT "#"
15:2 EOL "\n"
16:1 COMMENT "# Demonstrates a `accepts: <valtype>` generator. The valtype"
16:61 EOL "\n"
17:1 COMMENT "# path (`accepts: bool` here) is the one wired through emission;"
17:65 EOL "\n"
18:1 COMMENT "# reftype `accepts` is still on the deferred-polish list."
18:58 EOL "\n"
19:1 EOL "\n"
20:1 COMMENT "# Generator that emits the first two integers unconditionally,"
20:63 EOL "\n"
21:1 COMMENT "# then asks the caller whether to emit a third. The caller's"
21:61 EOL "\n"
22:1 COMMENT "# `bool` decision arrives via the second `.call value:`; the"
22:61 EOL "\n"
23:1 COMMENT "# expression-form yield binds it to `keep`."
23:44 EOL "\n"
